data.title: Charles Hibbert TUPPER
data.text:
Sir CHARLES HIBBERT TUPPER.

I know, an enormous piece of land. There were reasons for that, no doubt, whether good or bad. We have no explanation as to why such a tract of land was required or what the intention of the department is in regard to it.

Sir CHARLES HIBBERT TUPPER.

There may be a satisfactory explanation of what at first blush seems to be an exorbitant price, $9,000, for a site of this kind.
